title: Not Bad
text: I honestly think Subway Surfers is just a game you play when youâ€™re bored. You run miles on a subway track and you get coins and with those coins, you can buy new characters, awesome hoverboards, and different outfits. The game can sometimes hold new events and rank you on a leaderboard! (They show the results at the end of each month.) At first, it got me super addictive. Also, for any parents that are reading this, I donâ€™t mean â€œaddictedâ€ in a bad way. I mean that it gets you interested with all the cool features the game can do. It doesnâ€™t include chatting with other people, or any money (unless you want to buy any of the new characters, coins, or keys.) But like I said, I have better things to do, but in my free time, I really recommend Subway Surfers.

title: How to make a pancake :) ðŸ¥žðŸ¥žðŸ¥ž
text: You likely already have everything you need to make this pancake recipe. If not, here's what to add to your grocery list: Â· Flour: This homemade pancake recipe starts with all-purpose flour.â€¨Â· Baking powder: Baking powder, a leavener, is the secret to fluffy pancakes.â€¨Â· Sugar: Just a tablespoon of white sugar is all you'll need for subtly sweet pancakes.â€¨Â· Salt: A pinch of salt will enhance the overall flavor without making your pancakes taste salty.â€¨Â· Milk and butter: Milk and butter add moisture and richness to the pancakes.â€¨Â· Egg: A whole egg lends even more moisture. Plus, it helps bind the pancake batter together. How to Make Pancakes From Scratch It's not hard to make homemade pancakes â€” you just need a good recipe. That's where we come in! You'll find the step-by-step recipe below, but here's a brief overview of what you can expect: 1. Sift the dry ingredients together.â€¨2. Make a well, then add the wet ingredients. Stir to combine.â€¨3. Scoop the batter onto a hot griddle or pan.â€¨4. Cook for two to three minutes, then flip.â€¨5. Continue cooking until brown on both sides. When to Flip Pancakes Your pancake will tell you when it's ready to flip. Wait until bubbles start to form on the top and the edges look dry and set. This will usually take about two to three minutes on each side. How to Reheat Pancakes Store leftover pancakes in an airtight container in the fridge for about a week. Refrain from adding toppings (such as syrup) until right before you serve them so the pancakes don't get soggy.
